      • full

        public static int[][] full(int n)
        Returns a full set of bonds, such that each of the n points is joined to each of the others. Starts labeling points at 0.

      • full

        public static int[][] full(int n,
                           int first)
        Returns a full set of bonds, such that each of the n points is joined to each of the others; starts labeling of point using the given index . For example, full(3,2) returns {{2,3},{2,4},{3,4}}, which can be compared to full(3), which returns {{0,1},{0,2},{1,2}}

      • product

        public static int[][] product(int[] iSet)
        Prepares a set of bond pairs for a clusters formed from a disconnected set of fully connected subclusters.
        Parameters:
        iSet - element [k] describes the number of subclusters having k points
        Returns:
        int[][] the bond array built to the given specification
